Company Description


About Us
The first thing you learn at Leidos Australia is to leave current thinking at the door. Our aim is to make the world a safer, healthier and more efficient place, but we won’t get far using existing ideas. We need incisive minds like yours to weave together information technology, engineering and science skills into practical solutions for the most complex and high risk challenges.


Job Description


About your new role 
Are you an experienced security architect? Or, looking to transition from an engineering role? Do you believe that systems should be designed securely from the outset and not just validated at conclusion?
Working with a team of solution architects and engineers, you will be become a trusted security advisor to a Federal Government customer. You will collaboratively design secure systems that meet our customer’s needs. You will present new security and technology solutions to meet requirements whilst being part of a supportive and integrated team with peers in Pre-Sales, Project Management, Architecture, Engineering, and Security Architecture. You will be capable of building strong relationships working closely with customer stakeholders, Architecture and Security teams.
In a typical day, you will: 

Support security architecture services across project life cycles from concept, requirements, design, build, test verification and ongoing maintenance and support;
Documenting how the design follows the Australian Information Security Manual (ISM) for accreditation;
Providing design input into security functions in the design;
Preforming security risk assessments on the design;
Derive, review, interpret and respond to customer security requirements to ensure alignment between customer expectations and current and future road map technologies;
Work on security focused project activities to ensure requirements are captured and solutions align with the customer and Leidos strategic direction
Author and contribute to the design and definition of the security solution components contributing to High Level Designs (HLDs) and Detailed Level Designs (DLDs)
Engage with the Engineering team and CTO on solutions and alignment to existing and pipeline security solutions;
Work collaboratively with Engineering, Architecture and Security team to support security design compliance and governance activities with projects.



Qualifications


About you and what you'll bring:
You have demonstrated experience in:

Knowledge of applying defence frameworks such as ISM, DSPF and PSPF;
Experience in preparing security accreditation documentation;
Experience with working in a Defence in Depth environment;
Knowledge of OWASP and Essential Eight Maturity Model;
(Desirable) A Cybersecurity qualification, such as CISSP, CISM, CISA, CRISC, SSCP, CompTIA Security+, GIAC or equivalent background knowledge;
(Desirable) Worked with System Hardening (CIS benchmarks and ASD guidelines) and Vulnerability Assessments; and
Experience across the breadth of on-premise and cloud (Azure and M365) Microsoft technologies are also highly desirable.

This role does require the successful applicant to be an Australian Citizen, undergo an Australian Police Check and hold an active Baseline,  NV1 or NV2 clearance.


Additional Information


What You'll Love
This is a fast growing business currently implementing a range of business improvement initiatives, so you’ll have the chance to see some market leading technologies implemented across the function along with contributing to building further on the progressive work currently being developed. We offer a flexible working environment where it’s possible to design your ideal work week.
You’ll be joining a fun and friendly team who support each other closely and love to celebrate together.
Applicants may also need to meet International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) requirements. In certain circumstances this can place limitations on persons who hold dual nationality, permanent residency or are former nationals of certain countries as per ITAR 126.1.
